      "content": {
        "title": "Lumbar Disc Anatomy and Pathophysiology",
        "definition": "Nucleus pulposus herniation through annulus causing nerve root compression at L4-L5 and L5-S1.",
        "summary": "Central herniation causes cauda equina; lateral herniation causes radiculopathy."
